name: AllotmentInformation
definition: Information about the allotment of quantities of the issue to different subscribers. This relates a single instrument allotment against the subscription amounts allotted to each Subscriber.
label: allotment information

name: TradedInstrumentIssuanceProcessInformation
label: traded instrument issuance process information
definition: Information on one Security issue, arising from the Issuance Process. Note that one Issuance Process (Offering) may relate to more than on Issue, which itself may be the issue of more than one Traded Security.

name: PotentialUnderwriter
definition: The entity which will become the underwriter for an issue. Term origin:MBS PoC Reviews
label: potential underwriter

name: OfferingProcess
explanatoryNote: It is assumed that this exists for all security types as the precise issuance process is defined among the Offering terms. Terms which only exist for specific types of instrument are given as specialized variants of this class of Thing.
definition: The process step of offering a security for issue. This is the making available of a new securities issue through an underwriting.
label: offering

name: IssueSubscriptionInformation
definition: Information relating to the subscription of the issue.
label: issue subscription information

name: IssuedSecurityIssueInformation
label: issued security issue information
definition: Information about the Issuance of a Security, which is maintained throughout the life of the Security.

name: UnderwritingProcessDetails
label: underwriting process details
definition: Information specific to the Underwriting of the Issue.

name: SecuritiesIssuanceProcess
definition: The process by which a financial security is issued.
label: securities issuance process

name: SecondarySecurityOfferingDistribution
definition: An Offering of a security which has been previously issued.
label: secondary security offering distribution

name: SecurityOfferingDistributionMethod
label: security offering distribution method
definition: The distribution type of a securities Offering.

name: NegotiatedSaleMethod
definition: No definition
label: negotiated sale method

name: SecurityOfferingSaleMethod
definition: Method for sale of a new security offering.
label: security offering sale method

name: PrimaryIdentifierIssuer
definition: The party which formally issues the primary security identifier to the security. Term origin:MBS PoC Reviews
label: primary identifier issuer

name: CompetitiveSaleMethod
label: competitive sale method
definition: No definition

name: UnderwriterTakedown
definition: Infomation on Takedown quantity of the security handled by the underwriter (that will be brought into DTC).
label: underwriter takedown

name: RegistrationInformation
definition: Information relating to the registration of a registered security.
label: registration information

name: IssuanceProgramme
definition: A series of issuances over time.
label: issuance programme

name: PrimarySecurityOfferingDistribution
definition: The original sale of a company's securities, in which the proceeds from the sale are received directly by the company.
label: primary security offering distribution

name: firstTradeDateAndTime
label: first trade date and time
definition: First Date and Time a trade may be executed for this security. All times in Eastern Time Zone only. NOTE: This is a date in the future tense at the time of the Offering.

name: issueNominalNumberOfUnits
label: issue nominal number of units
definition: Total original quantity of securities issued.

name: series
definition: Series identification for the individual Traded Financial Security.
label: series

name: actualClosingDate
definition: The Closing Date for the Issue, recorded after the event.
label: actual closing date

name: underwriterTakedownShares
definition: Takedown quantity of the security handled by the underwriter (that will be brought into DTC).
label: underwriter takedown shares

name: offerIssueSeries
label: series
definition: Uniquely identified collection of securities within an Issue with same Expected Closing Date. The text gives the Series Identifier within the Issuance process. There may be one or more Series within one Issue.

name: formalAwardDateAndTime
definition: Date and time the issuer formally accepts a bid for Competitive Issues or, the Date and Time the Bond Purchase Agreement is executed for Negotiated Issues. Time Zone: Include in date/time data or add a term for it?
label: formal award date and time

name: expectedClosingDate
definition: The date on which the transfer of positions to underwriters is expected to take place. This date is provided by underwriters as part of an announcement.
label: expected closing date

name: subscriptionPeriod
definition: Period during which the security can be subscribed to.
label: subscription period

name: hasSaleMethod
definition: Sale Method of the security.
label: has sale method

name: overAlloted
definition: Whether the subscriber has been over-alloted the requested number of units. REVIEW: Not seen in data terms but implied elsewhere.
label: over alloted

name: issueOfferingUnits
label: issue offering units
definition: Quantity of all securities that is offered in an equity or Corporate Bond issue.

name: firstTradeDate
label: first trade date
definition: The date of the first trade of the security in the secondary market.

name: announcementDate
definition: Date/time, as announced by the issuer, at which the securities were to be issued and subsequently were issued.
label: announcement date

name: firstTradeSettlementDate
definition: The date the Issuer and Underwriter exchange money for bonds.
label: first trade settlement date

name: hasPartiallyPaidIssuanceSchedule
label: has partially paid issuance schedule
definition: Partially paid issue: Schedule of partial payments and dates.

name: minimumIssueSubscription
label: minimum issue subscription
definition: Minimum or incremental denomination required for the transfer or change of ownership of a security.

name: subscriptionAmount
definition: Number of units of the issue that an individual subscriber is allocated.
label: subscription amount
